        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>June 8. 1871</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I thank you very sincerely for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> kind letter, &amp; for your notes, which shall be duly considered whenever I have to prepare a corrected edition of my last book—<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>The judgment of a man who like you, has made one of the most wonderful expeditions on record, certainly deserves the fullest consideration.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>With respect to the colour of desert animals I trusted to M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Tristram, who I believe visited the borders of, if he did not penetrate into the Sahara.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>With great respect I beg leave to remain | dear Sir | yours faithfully &amp; obliged | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7805.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Gerhard Rohlfs, 6 June 1871</ref> and nn. 8, 12, and 13. CD refers to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Rohlfs was the first European to explore and map the Libyan desert (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5820.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">NDB</hi></ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4808.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Henry Baker Tristram</ref>. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7805.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Gerhard Rohlfs, 6 June 1871</ref> and n. 12.</note>
        </div>        
            
